description: This village in central Bedfordshire lies just to the east of Woburn Sands in the county. Local options include the cycling and walking trails in nearby Aspley Woods and the popular Milton Keynes Boundary Walk which can be picked up just to the west. The village also has a train station making it easily accessible by public transport. This circular walk uses part of the Milton Keynes Boundary walk to visit Woburn Sands and Aspley Heath and Woods. The expansive woods are a popular place for walkers and mountain bikers with miles of woodland trails to explore.
